{
  "texts": [
    "Consider the null data in Fig. 5H that is matched in spike phases; spike positions, however, are randomly chosen from a uniform distribution.",
    "In the large spike count limit, uniformly distributed activity should not convey any information.",
    "Yet, the null data show more position information per spike during sparser phases (Fig. 5G).",
    "To correct for this bias, we follow previous protocols and subtract averages over many null-matched samples from position information 48.",
    "In all of our comparisons of information between sparse and dense phases, including the model prediction in Fig. 5A, we report sparsity-corrected information."
  ]
}